claim.claim-text:
1. An active matrix type liquid crystal display apparatus including driving means having an active element, comprising: 
an electrode structure mainly applying an electric field which is substantially parallel to a substrate surface to a liquid crystal layer; 
at least a part of a portion of a signal wiring which opposes to the liquid crystal layer transmitting a video signal to said active element and is covered by a conductive material via an insulator; 
said conductive material being electrically connected with a common electrode as one of electrodes of said electrode structure which mainly applies the electric field to the liquid crystal layer.

2. An active matrix type liquid crystal display apparatus having at least one transparent substrate of a pair of transparent substrates and a liquid crystal layer between said substrates, wherein 
an electrode structure forming an electric field applied to said liquid crystal layer and an active element are provided on one of said pair of substrates; 
at least a part of a portion of a signal wiring which opposes the liquid crystal layer and transmits a video signal to said active element and is covered by a conductive material via an insulator; 
said electrode structure being formed with a pixel electrode and a common electrode; and 
said conductive material being electrically connected to said common electrode.
